# Mobile Build Configuration

This file contains environment variables and settings needed for building iOS and Android apps.

## Setup Instructions

1. Copy this file: `cp .env.mobile.example .env.mobile`
2. Fill in the values below
3. Use when building: `source .env.mobile && npm run mobile:build`

---

## iOS Configuration

```bash
# iOS Team ID (from Apple Developer account)
# Find in: Apple Developer account → Membership → Team ID
IOS_TEAM_ID=XXXXXXXXXX

# iOS Bundle ID (must match App Store Connect)
IOS_BUNDLE_ID=com.qmedpro.app

# iOS App Store ID (from App Store Connect after app creation)
IOS_APP_ID=123456789

# iOS Distribution Certificate Path
IOS_CERT_PATH=./certs/ios_distribution.cer

# iOS Provisioning Profile Path
IOS_PROVISIONING_PROFILE=./certs/ios_provisioning_profile.mobileprovision
```

## Android Configuration

```bash
# Android Package Name (must match Play Console)
ANDROID_PACKAGE_NAME=com.qmedpro.app

# Android Keystore Path (for signing APK/AAB)
ANDROID_KEYSTORE_PATH=./certs/qmedpro-key.jks

# Android Keystore Password
ANDROID_KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=changeme

# Android Key Alias (from keytool)
ANDROID_KEY_ALIAS=qmedpro

# Android Key Password
ANDROID_KEY_PASSWORD=changeme

# Android App Version Code (increment for each release)
ANDROID_VERSION_CODE=1

# Android App Version Name
ANDROID_VERSION_NAME=1.0.0
```

## App Store Connect Credentials

```bash
# Apple ID Email (for App Store Connect access)
APPLE_ID_EMAIL=your-email@example.com

# Apple ID App-Specific Password (generated in account settings)
APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD=xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx

# Apple ID Team Name
APPLE_TEAM_NAME="Your Team Name"
```

## Google Play Console Credentials

```bash
# Google Play Service Account Email
GOOGLE_PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=your-email@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com

# Google Play Service Account Key (base64 encoded)
GOOGLE_PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY=eyJhbGc...

# Google Play Application ID
GOOGLE_PLAY_APPLICATION_ID=com.qmedpro.app
```

## Common Settings

```bash
# App Name (appears on device home screen)
APP_NAME=QMed Pro

# App Version (shown in stores)
APP_VERSION=1.0.0

# Support Email (displayed in app)
SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@qmedpro.com

# Website URL (for privacy policy links)
WEBSITE_URL=https://qmedpro.com

# Privacy Policy URL (required by stores)
PRIVACY_POLICY_URL=https://qmedpro.com/privacy

# Terms of Service URL (required by stores)
TERMS_OF_SERVICE_URL=https://qmedpro.com/terms
```

## Development vs Production

```bash
# Environment: development | staging | production
ENVIRONMENT=development

# API Base URL
API_BASE_URL=https://api.qmedpro.com

# Enable Debug Logging
DEBUG=false

# Enable Crash Reporting
CRASH_REPORTING_ENABLED=false
```

---

## How to Generate Required Files

### 1. iOS Certificates

```bash
# In Apple Developer Portal:
# 1. Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles → Certificates
# 2. Create "Apple Distribution" certificate
# 3. Download .cer file
# 4. Save to ./certs/ios_distribution.cer
```

### 2. iOS Provisioning Profile

```bash
# In Apple Developer Portal:
# 1. Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles → Provisioning Profiles
# 2. Create "App Store" provisioning profile
# 3. Download .mobileprovision file
# 4. Save to ./certs/ios_provisioning_profile.mobileprovision
```

### 3. Android Signing Key

```bash
keytool -genkey -v -keystore ./certs/qmedpro-key.jks \
  -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000 \
  -alias qmedpro
```

### 4. Google Play Service Account Key

```bash
# In Google Cloud Console:
# 1. Create service account for Google Play API
# 2. Generate JSON key
# 3. Base64 encode: cat key.json | base64
# 4. Paste into GOOGLE_PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY
```

---

## Security Notes

⚠️ **NEVER commit this file to version control!**

Add to `.gitignore`:
```
.env.mobile
certs/
*.jks
*.cer
*.mobileprovision
```

Store credentials securely:
- Use environment variable secrets in CI/CD
- Keep physical key files in password-protected storage
- Rotate credentials regularly
- Use different credentials for dev/staging/production

---

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| **Missing BUILD_TOOLS_VERSION** | Update Android SDK in Android Studio |
| **Provisioning profile expired** | Regenerate in Apple Developer Portal |
| **Keystore not found** | Ensure path is relative to project root |
| **Bundle ID mismatch** | Verify matches App Store Connect |

---

For detailed instructions, see: `APP_STORE_DEPLOYMENT.md`
